Anti-apartheid struggle stalwart Ahmed Kathrada. Struggle veteran Ahmed Kathrada has died his foundation said on Tuesday morning. He was 87 years old. In a tweet at 5.43am the foundation said: &#8220;Ahmed #Kathrada has passed on. Details to follow.&#8221; The Nelson Mandela Foundation mourned the death of the ANC stalwart. &#8220;We are deeply saddened to learn this morning of the passing on of our dear friend &amp; founding trustee Ahmed #Kathrada &#8221; the foundation tweeted. &#8220;Hamba Kahle Kathy.&#8221; Kathrada had been ill for the last month with his condition deteriorating in the last 24 hours. He was taken in for surgery linked to blood clotting on the brain. The Ahmed Kathrada Foundation s Director Neeshan Balton said that the veteran had experienced several post-operation complications rendering his condition serious . Kathrada has contracted pneumonia which has affected both his lungs Balton said. Despite appropriate medical care his condition is deteriorating. He is currently comfortable. There was an immediate outpouring of grief on the social media platform. This is a developing story. Related Share on Facebook Share Share on Twitter Tweet Share on Google Plus Share